name: Urethal Obstruction
description: A blockage in the urethra that can cause difficulty urinating and other urinary issues.

name: Feline Lower Urinary Tract Disease
description: A group of conditions affecting the lower urinary tract; often causing discomfort and frequent urination.

name: Renal Disease
description: Chronic kidney disease that impairs the kidney function and can lead to various symptoms and complications.

name: Luxation
description: Dislocation or displacement of a joint; causing pain and mobility issues.

name: Panleukopenia
description: A highly contagious viral disease that affects the gastrointestinal tract and immune system.

name: Intestinal Parasites
description: Infections caused by various parasites that affect the gastrointestinal system.

name: Hairball Obstruction
description: Accumulation of hair in the stomach or intestines; causing blockages and discomfort.

name: Scabies
description: A skin infestation caused by mites; leading to intense itching and skin irritation.

name: Flea Allergy
description: An allergic reaction to flea bites; causing skin inflammation and discomfort.

name: Atopic Dermatitis
description: Chronic skin inflammation and itching caused by allergic reactions to environmental factors.
